What should you do when your software breaks, when your labs don't work out,
when your tests are bombed, when your homework has errors?  These are questions
every instructor has faced.

Inspired by the SIGCSE 2007 panel on "Teaching Tips We Wish They'd Told Us
Before We Started," I'm interested in gathering tips and techniques to share
with new engineering educators at next year's ASEE conference.  I'd be
interested in hearing from you if you ...

-- have any techniques or anecdotes to mention,
-- have seen any other articles on the subject, or
-- know of other listservs where I could post the same query.

I think this survey could turn out to be a great resource.  I know I could often
use it myself!

I will, of course, be happy to share my conclusions with this list, either when
the paper is finished next January, or piecemeal earlier upon request.

